keyFacts: Jeffrey Epstein's passport number was P110708878.
The document records 40 travel encounters for Epstein between April 1991 and September 2000.
Primary travel hubs were JFK in New York and LHR in London, with frequent flights between them.
Several entries indicate travel without Advanced Passenger Information (APIS), noted as 'AIRLINE (NOT API)'.
The document was generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on January 23, 2020, suggesting it was compiled for investigative purposes long after the travel occurred.
